The Catalan giants will be hoping Neymar can produce the kind of clinical streak he showed during the World Cup before his injury, as he became Brazil's sixth all-time top goalscorer overtaking Ronaldinho in the process.

After netting 17 times in 42 appearances last term as Barcelona endured a trophy-less season, the young Brazilian and his team will most certainly be looking to raise the stakes in La Liga this time around.

